Job   Description   Summary  JOB   PURPOSE      To   assist   technical   services   management   by   performing   technical   analysis   of   manufacturing   processes    systems    heat   treat    N  C   programming    cellular   manufacturing    etc    to   permit   effective   management   decisions          JOB   RELATED   STATISTICS      Indeterminate  JOB   DUTIES      This   is   a   staff   assignment   that    independently   or   as   part   of   a   team    is   involved   in   the   maintenance   and   improvement   of   processes   and   systems   used   in   the   manufacture   of   product   This   is   a   fully   functioning   journey   level   position    for   an   incumbent   with   a   varied   amount   of   remanufacturing   experience    who   may   obtain   assistance   from   a   more   experienced   senior   level   person      Troubleshoots   day  to  day   process   problems    initiates   solutions    and   follows  up   to   evaluate   effectiveness   of   changes   to   ensure   practical   cleaning    salvage    machining    fabrication    assembly    testing    storing    packing   and   moving   of   production   material   within   the   components   group      Designs   or   directs   the   acquisition    design    fabrication   and   repair   of   all   necessary   tooling   and   machines      Monitors   all   exchange   and   in  house   requirements    monitors   salvage   rates    analyzes   core   receipts   and   schedules   and   procures   all   new   parts   necessary   to   meet   schedules      Determines    contacts   and   negotiates   with   external   suppliers   for   machines    tooling    parts   and   contracted   labor      Analyzes   engineering   change   notices    determines   any   part   or   process   change    initiates   and   implements   all   changes      Establishes   and   maintain   bill   of   materials   and   work   orders   to   support   cost   management   system      Answers   one  on  one   end   customer   complainants   or   questions   and   make   any   required   process   changes      Assumes   day  to  day   coaching   duties   in   absence   of   team   leader       Analyzes   and   recommends   current   and   future   systems    procedures    training   and   equipment   needs   based   upon   understanding   and   communication   with   users      Determines   acceptability   of   new   equipment   based   on   usage   requirements   and   recommends   modification   or   revision   as   necessary   Provides   analysis   and   recommendations   needed   to   allow   manufacturing   to   produce   the   engineering   product   designs      Provides   effective   communication   and   services   in   solving   production   problems   or   pursuing   operations   improvements      Simulates   present   and   future   machine   lines   and   cells   to   predict   line   flow   problems   and   makes   recommendations   for   implementation   Conducts   investigation   to   assist   in   resolving   heat   treat   mechanical   and   technical   problems      Performs   quality   checks   on   equipment    fluids    etc    used   in   heat   treat   operations   and   coordinates   heat   treat   start   up   and   shut   down   procedures   before   and   after   extended   shut   down   periods       Adheres Job   Description   Summary  JOB   PURPOSE      To   assist   technical   services   management   by   performing   technical   analysis   of   manufacturing   processes    systems    heat   treat    N  C   programming    cellular   manufacturing    etc    to   permit   effective   management   decisions          JOB   RELATED   STATISTICS      Indeterminate  JOB   DUTIES      This   is   a   staff   assignment   that    independently   or   as   part   of   a   team    is   involved   in   the   maintenance   and   improvement   of   processes   and   systems   used   in   the   manufacture   of   product   This   is   a   fully   functioning   journey   level   position    for   an   incumbent   with   a   varied   amount   of   remanufacturing   experience    who   may   obtain   assistance   from   a   more   experienced   senior   level   person      Troubleshoots   day  to  day   process   problems    initiates   solutions    and   follows  up   to   evaluate   effectiveness   of   changes   to   ensure   practical   cleaning    salvage    machining    fabrication    assembly    testing    storing    packing   and   moving   of   production   material   within   the   components   group      Designs   or   directs   the   acquisition    design    fabrication   and   repair   of   all   necessary   tooling   and   machines      Monitors   all   exchange   and   in  house   requirements    monitors   salvage   rates    analyzes   core   receipts   and   schedules   and   procures   all   new   parts   necessary   to   meet   schedules      Determines    contacts   and   negotiates   with   external   suppliers   for   machines    tooling    parts   and   contracted   labor      Analyzes   engineering   change   notices    determines   any   part   or   process   change    initiates   and   implements   all   changes      Establishes   and   maintain   bill   of   materials   and   work   orders   to   support   cost   management   system      Answers   one  on  one   end   customer   complainants   or   questions   and   make   any   required   process   changes      Assumes   day  to  day   coaching   duties   in   absence   of   team   leader       Analyzes   and   recommends   current   and   future   systems    procedures    training   and   equipment   needs   based   upon   understanding   and   communication   with   users      Determines   acceptability   of   new   equipment   based   on   usage   requirements   and   recommends   modification   or   revision   as   necessary   Provides   analysis   and   recommendations   needed   to   allow   manufacturing   to   produce   the   engineering   product   designs      Provides   effective   communication   and   services   in   solving   production   problems   or   pursuing   operations   improvements      Simulates   present   and   future   machine   lines   and   cells   to   predict   line   flow   problems   and   makes   recommendations   for   implementation   Conducts   investigation   to   assist   in   resolving   heat   treat   mechanical   and   technical   problems      Performs   quality   checks   on   equipment    fluids    etc    used   in   heat   treat   operations   and   coordinates   heat   treat   start   up   and   shut   down   procedures   before   and   after   extended   shut   down   periods       Adheres   to   established   standards    policies   and   practices   relating   to   quality    cost   reduction    safety    ergonomics    etc    in   performing   assigned   duties     职 类   数 分析师   关键字    数  数字化  数挖掘    微信 分享
